Project description

This library provides Python bindings for the Libosmium C++library, a library for working with OpenStreetMap data in a fast and flexiblemanner.

Installation

pyosmium can be installed with pip:

pip install osmium

The Pypi source package already comes bundled with a matching version oflibosmium, protozero and pybind11. Pyosmium additionally depends onexpat, libz, libbz2 and Boost variant and iterator. You need to installdevelopment packages for these libraries. On Debian/Ubuntu do:

sudo apt-get install build-essential cmake libboost-dev \                   libexpat1-dev zlib1g-dev libbz2-dev

Python >= 3.6 is supported. Pypy is known not to work.

Documentation

The documentation for the latest release is available atosmcode.org.

If you find bugs or have feature requests, please report those in theGithub issue tracker. For general questions about using pyosmium youcan contanct the OSM development mailing list or ask on OSM help.

Examples

The package contains an example directory with small examples on how to usethe library. They are mostly ports of the examples in Libosmium andosmium-contrib.

Fineprint

Pyosmium is available under the BSD 2-Clause License. See LICENSE.TXT.

The source code can be found on GitHub.
